YOU DON’T GET WHAT YOU DESERVE!👇🏼

You get what you tolerate in life! 

You get what you work for. 

You get what you focus on. 

You get what you commit to.

You get what you sweat for. 

Here’s the reality about life… IT’S HARD! 

It’s hard by design, because this world rewards those who are willing to do the work that’s required. 

It rewards those who are willing to sweat, focus, commit and pay their dues!

There is no other way. 

EVERYBODY WANTS TO EAT, BUT  very Few will Hunt 🦅

SUCCESS IS NOT FOR THE IMPATIENT!👇🏼

Want to get lean and jacked? 💪🏾 It’s going to take patience. 

Want to stack millions? 💰 It’s going to take patience. 

Want a deep meaningful relationship? 👫 It’s going to take patience.

Want to be known and famous? It’s going to take patience. 

EVERYTHING GREAT THAT YOU WANT FROM LIFE IS ON THE OTHER SIDE OF PATIENCE. 

You can have the best product or service. You can have the best marketing. You can buy all the blue check marks out there… 

…but unless you can be aggressively patient you’re never going to make it to the top! 

Aggressive patience is letting go of short term thinking and committing to doing the unsexy work, in a focused fashion, over a period of time ! 

In today’s world of immediate gratification the compounding factor of aggressive patience is overlooked because so many of you have become conditioned to want the outcome before you’ve even paid your dues! 

That’s not how the game works! 

All success compounds over time and with focused work. 

I measure my short term goals by 5 years and my long terms goals by a decade+

…while most measuring they goals by days and months! 

Wake up! Develop aggressive patience, get focused, and do the goddamn work! 💰🔨

No one else will be this honest with you, so it’s on me to be! 

Happy Sunday ! 🦍

THIS IS AN IRREFUTABLE FACT!👇🏼

Your eyes will always find what your head and heart are looking for. 

 - YOUR FREQUENCY IS WHAT YOU FREQUENTLY SEE. 

There’s no way around it! You can’t have a negative perception but expect a positive outcome. 

You will always find evidence if you’re looking for it!!! 

If you’re always worried about money, then you’ll always be worried about money…

…that’s because we attract what we think about the most! 

These 3 things will produce the fruit you are looking for in your life 👇🏾

Intention - Frequency - Action!

Imagine just how weird it would be if we were all born as our highest self? 

Like if you were born self actualized and knew the meaning of life? 

How freaking sad would that be? 

The rest of life would be boring and uneventful. 

Thank GOD we're all born average at best and we experience life's ups and downs so that we can problem solve through these experiences and figure out who we really are and what our purpose and calling in life will be. 

You see, the purpose of life is to figure out YOUR purpose in life...

...its for this reason that we are all born average and are given life's challenges so that we have the opportunity to become our higher selves through the process of problem solving. 

The higher self is the version of you who has emotional resilience, compassion, kindness, self control, discipline and self awareness. 

The higher self is the version of you who is both a savage and a servant. 

The higher self is the version of you who is enlightened and purpose driven rather than a pleasure driven and approval seeking. 

The higher self is the version of you who is confident in who he is mentally, emotionally and physically. 

THE HIGHER SELF IS UNFUCKWITHABLE 💰😤

But here's the sad reality about most of humanity: Most people stay average and never evolve. 

The average man inspires no one. 

And this is why most people suffer in silence, feel lost and without purpose, succumb to vices, have poor relationships and are always fat, tired and anxious. 

Take no joy in mediocrity or being average - fight to elevate to your highest self friends! 💎✊🏾

Pay it forward. Share this.

Nuts! Unreasonable! Intense! Unrealistic! 

They’ll call you all of these until you make it and then when you do, they’ll say: “they knew you’d make it all along.” 

I lost count how many friends and family members told me I was in over my head and being unrealistic when I was coming up. 

It’s not that they didn’t want me to succeed… it’s because they were transferring their own limiting beliefs on me. 

They didn’t see what I saw in my head. 

They didn’t feel what I felt in my heart. 

They didn’t have the burning desire that raged within me. 

They didn’t have the work ethic that I had… 

…and so they’d transfer their feelings of mediocrity and then tell me I was nuts, too intense and unreasonable for wanting it all! 

Listen, there are gonna be all types of people in your life who won’t see your heart, won’t understand your drive and will never have your hunger. NEVER LISTEN TO THEM. 

Not even for a second! 

You think big! You do the work! You get paid! You live an extraordinary life! 

They think small. They’re allergic to hard work. They’ll live a life of mediocrity. 

Here’s to all of you out there coming up who are dreaming big and putting in the work at night, on weekends and when no one is looking! 

Show them how nuts you really are! 👊🏼❤️

Your story, it’s the ONLY thing that’s holding you back. 

The story you keep telling yourself. 

The story you keep telling others about yourself. 

The story of why you failed, why you’re the victim, why you were wronged and why you can’t is what’s holding you back in life. 

See each time you tell your story to yourself or others, you then go out and look for evidence to prove your story right. 

It’s like a self-of feeling prophecy. 

If you want things to change for you then change your story! 

Stop talking about what went wrong, or why you can’t, or how you got wronged and start rewriting your story of how you win. 

Your life is like a book that’s only half full…

…so you can either focus on the earlier pages or you can take the pen back and start writing a new story in the empty pages that remain. 

Change your story, change your life!
